@*Create.cshtml

This Razor page facilitates the creation of assignments within the e-learning application. Here's a summary of its key features:

- Utilizes the `elearningapp.Models.Assignments` model.
- Sets the page title to "Create".
- Provides a form for users to input assignment details.
- Routes the form submission to the "Create" action.
- Displays model-level validation errors in red.
- Allows users to input Course ID, Title, Description, and Due Date for the assignment.
- The "Create" button submits the form to create the assignment.
- Includes a "Back to List" link for returning to the list page.

This page streamlines the process of creating assignments in the e-learning application. *@

@model elearningapp.Models.Assignments

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Create";
}

<h1>Create</h1>

<h4>Assignments</h4>
<hr />
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <form asp-action="Create">
            <div asp-validation-summary="ModelOnly" class="text-danger"></div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="CourseId" class="control-label"></label>
                <input asp-for="CourseId" class="form-control" />
                <span asp-validation-for="CourseId" class="text-danger"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="Title" class="control-label"></label>
                <input asp-for="Title" class="form-control" />
                <span asp-validation-for="Title" class="text-danger"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="Description" class="control-label"></label>
                <input asp-for="Description" class="form-control" />
                <span asp-validation-for="Description" class="text-danger"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label asp-for="DueDate" class="control-label"></label>
                <input asp-for="DueDate" class="form-control" />
                <span asp-validation-for="DueDate" class="text-danger"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <input type="submit" value="Create" class="btn btn-primary" />
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>

<div>
    <a asp-action="Index">Back to List</a>
</div>

@section Scripts {
    @{await Html.RenderPartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial");}
}
